{"title":"Risk Response Plan","markdown":{"headingText":"Risk Response Plan","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n## Purpose of This Document\n\nThis Risk Response Plan defines **how identified project risks will be\nhandled**, detailing:\n\n- Risk ownership\n- Response strategies (avoid, mitigate, accept, escalate)\n- Trigger conditions\n- Contingency and fallback actions\n- Integration with KPIs and Stage‑Gates\n\nThis document operationalizes the **Risk Register** and is a **mandatory PMBOK\nPlanning artifact**.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Management Principles\n\n1. **Ecological risks take precedence** over schedule and cost risks  \n2. No efficiency gain justifies increased ecological risk  \n3. Risk responses must be:\n   - Predefined\n   - Actionable\n   - Auditable\n4. KPI‑3 (Ecological Data Protection Index) is the primary risk sentinel\n\n---\n\n## Risk Categorization\n\nRisks are managed in four categories:\n\n- **Environmental / Ecological**\n- **Data & Technical**\n- **Operational**\n- **Governance & Adoption**\n\nEach category has predefined escalation paths.\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Risk Response Table\n\n### R1 — Ecological Data Loss (False Negatives)\n\n| Element | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Risk ID | R1 |\n| Description | Automated screening incorrectly excludes benthic‑relevant imagery |\n| Category | Environmental / Ecological |\n| Probability | Medium |\n| Impact | **Very High** |\n| Primary KPI | KPI‑3 (Ecological Data Protection Index) |\n| Owner | Environmental SME Lead |\n\n**Response Strategy**\n\n- **Mitigate / Avoid**\n\n**Preventive Actions**\n\n- Precision‑first model design\n- Conservative thresholds\n- SME‑approved annotation guidelines\n\n**Trigger**\n\n- KPI‑3 < agreed threshold (85–90%)\n\n**Contingency Actions**\n\n- Immediate halt of automated filtering\n- Re‑screen affected datasets manually\n- Model retraining with SME‑reviewed samples\n\n**Escalation**\n\n- Immediate escalation to Sponsor\n- Stage‑Gate progression blocked\n\n---\n\n### R2 — Annotation Subjectivity\n\n| Element | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Risk ID | R2 |\n| Description | Inconsistent labels due to expert interpretation differences |\n| Category | Data / Ecological |\n| Probability | High |\n| Impact | High |\n| Primary KPI | KPI‑4 (Cross‑Field Ecological Consistency) |\n| Owner | Environmental SME Lead |\n\n**Response Strategy**\n\n- **Mitigate**\n\n**Preventive Actions**\n\n- Formal annotation guidelines\n- Consensus labeling sessions\n- Periodic inter‑annotator agreement checks\n\n**Trigger**\n\n- Significant deviation in validation metrics across annotators or fields\n\n**Contingency Actions**\n\n- Reconciliation workshops\n- Guideline refinement\n- Label correction cycles\n\n---\n\n### R3 — Model Underperformance\n\n| Element | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Risk ID | R3 |\n| Description | Model does not reach minimum performance criteria |\n| Category | Technical |\n| Probability | Medium |\n| Impact | High |\n| Primary KPI | KPI‑3, KPI‑1 |\n| Owner | Data Science Lead |\n\n**Response Strategy**\n\n- **Mitigate / Accept (MVP)**\n\n**Preventive Actions**\n\n- Incremental training\n- Balanced validation sets\n- Conservative success thresholds\n\n**Trigger**\n\n- Repeated failure to meet MVP criteria after retraining\n\n**Contingency Actions**\n\n- Restrict usage to assisted annotation only\n- Extend MVP timeline\n- Escalate decision to Sponsor\n\n---\n\n### R4 — Class Imbalance Bias\n\n| Element | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Risk ID | R4 |\n| Description | Non‑benthic dominance biases model learning |\n| Category | Data |\n| Probability | High |\n| Impact | Medium |\n| Owner | Data Science Lead |\n\n**Response Strategy**\n\n- **Mitigate**\n\n**Preventive Actions**\n\n- Weighted loss functions\n- Controlled sampling\n- Validation on balanced subsets\n\n**Trigger**\n\n- Drop in benthic recall or retention metrics\n\n**Contingency Actions**\n\n- Rebalance training data\n- Adjust loss weighting\n- SME review of failure cases\n\n---\n\n### R5 — Data Quality Degradation\n\n| Element | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Risk ID | R5 |\n| Description | Poor image quality (turbidity, lighting) affects screening |\n| Category | Data / Operational |\n| Probability | High |\n| Impact | Medium |\n| Owner | Data Engineering Lead |\n\n**Response Strategy**\n\n- **Mitigate / Accept**\n\n**Preventive Actions**\n\n- Quality filtering rules\n- Flagging unusable data\n\n**Trigger**\n\n- High proportion of unusable frames\n\n**Contingency Actions**\n\n- Exclude degraded data from automation\n- Manual review fallback\n\n---\n\n### R6 — Stakeholder Misalignment\n\n| Element | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Risk ID | R6 |\n| Description | Divergent expectations between technical and environmental stakeholders |\n| Category | Governance |\n| Probability | Medium |\n| Impact | High |\n| Owner | Project Manager |\n\n**Response Strategy**\n\n- **Mitigate**\n\n**Preventive Actions**\n\n- OKR and KPI transparency\n- Frequent checkpoints\n\n**Trigger**\n\n- Conflicting feedback at validation points\n\n**Contingency Actions**\n\n- Alignment workshop\n- Sponsor arbitration\n\n---\n\n### R7 — Adoption Resistance\n\n| Element | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Risk ID | R7 |\n| Description | Low trust or usage of automated outputs |\n| Category | Operational |\n| Probability | Medium |\n| Impact | Medium |\n| Owner | Product Owner |\n\n**Response Strategy**\n\n- **Mitigate / Accept**\n\n**Preventive Actions**\n\n- SME involvement from start\n- Explainability and transparency\n\n**Trigger**\n\n- Low utilization or negative feedback\n\n**Contingency Actions**\n\n- Restrict usage to advisory mode\n- Additional training and communication\n\n---\n\n## Risk–Stage‑Gate Integration\n\n| Stage‑Gate | Critical Risks Reviewed |\n|----------|------------------------|\n| G1 | R1, R2 |\n| G2 | R1, R2, R3 |\n| G3 | R1, R3, R7 |\n| G4 | R1, R5, R6 |\n\nFailure of **R1 controls** automatically blocks gate progression.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Monitoring and Reporting\n\n- Risk Register reviewed **weekly**\n- High and critical risks reported to Sponsor\n- KPI‑based risk triggers monitored continuously\n- Risk responses logged for auditability\n\n---\n\n## Residual Risk Acceptance\n\nResidual risks may only be accepted when:\n\n- Ecological risk is explicitly acknowledged\n- Acceptance is documented\n- Sponsor approval is obtained\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":true,"code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true,"format-links":["html","pdf"]},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","metadata-files":["../location/pt.yml"],"toc":true,"css":["../styles.css"],"html-math-method":"mathjax","embed-resou